Does Summer make you happy or depressed? 🌞

I am genuinely curious what other people think because a lot of us have a image of what Summer is “supposed” to look like.

It’s completely normal to experience “summertime sadness” that can manifest in a number of ways. A lot has to do with the expectation that Summer will “fix” everything or be the “greatest Summer ever”. Some just hate how hot 🥵it gets haha.

Whether you have good ol’ year round depression or just certain aspects of the season brings you down here are some tips I’ve used: 

- stay hydrated 💦I know this can sound stupid but studies show when your body doesn’t have enough water, it causes a shortage of amino acids which can make you feel irritable and anxious. 
- keep a good sleeping schedule because lack of sleep can actually worsen a persons depression.
- stay active whether it’s inside or outside…I shouldn’t have to explain this you know after 20-30 mins you’ll feel better with that dopamine boost⚡️. 
- get outside for that vitamin D except always use SPF don’t waste time burning stay in your glow ✨
- make time for yourself and also make sure you socialize! Loneliness can feed on itself and it’s easy to get stuck in a hard cycle. Push yourself a bit to putting yourself out there.
- don’t set unrealistic expectations on yourself or the season you got all year! I mean literally your entire life ✨💜

#mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealthawarenessmonth #lifestyle #soberliving #summer #summervibes #healthylifestyle

Are there benefits to wake and bake ? 😂💚💨

This might sound crazy to the regular Jo that doesn’t smoke very often and that’s okay! I wanted to share some benefits I’ve seen with my experience:

- I create my morning wellness routine around it. This helps me form a basis for a productive day. Wake and bake helps me take a moment to relax in the morning. 🌞

- Helps mentally calm me when preparing for my day. I get a lot of anxiety when my day involves tons of social interactions 🙈. Having this breather helps recalibrate and prepare myself to approach the day. 

- This one is kinda crazy but no joke I have 10x more stamina in my workouts after a wake and bake. I tend to be able to run longer and zone out easier. 🏃‍♀️

Waking and baking isn’t something degenerates do…we’ll it can be😂. But that doesn’t mean smoking in the morning is a bad idea. If you can use the help in the morning I think there’s nothing wrong with experimenting. It may inspire you to have a better and more productive day.✨

I love using @huxtonusa energy strain it’s been my go to! ⚡️

#mentalhealthawarenessmonth #mentalhealthawareness #lifestyle #summerbreak #morningroutine #vlog

Here are my tips to enjoy Cannabis for relaxation at the end of the day 💚✨

- Choose the right strain! I love Huxton’s relax and rejuvenate Indica joints. It’s Indica dominant and that’s exactly what you want for sleep and calm vibes😴 

- Creating a nighttime routine! I love doing the sauna and cold plunge in the evening it can help your body release melatonin. I like ending my days by going to the beach to meditate and smoke. Creating a routine like this  personally helps me maintain a healthy balance with cannabis. 🤜🏼🤛🏼

- Avoid electronics 📱 mainly the phone it’s a stimulant! Just try and give your self 30 minutes to mediate go to the beach do whatever to relax (smoke a joint 😉). 

- Make your smoke sesh a reason to get out of the house! I love going to the beach to relax be by myself and smoke a lil doobie. Listen to the waves to help clear my head.🌊 Or go on a sunset hike! Just get outside. 🌞

Regardless of whether you smoke or not try to create a routine! Nighttime routines help your brain distinguish the day from the night, clear your mind and body of the day’s stresses, and fall asleep peacefully. 🌕

4 things I do when I get Summertime Sadness✨: 

- Try not to Isolate. 🫶🏼
It can be so easy and depression creates this. It wants you to feel alone. It can make things feel worst. I remind myself that I have to let people in and I do my best at easing back into the crazy world 🫶🏼 Isolation won’t heal you 

- Do something that makes you laugh. ✨
I have plenty of dark days where getting out of bed can seem impossible. I push myself to fight it by finding something that makes me laugh I’ll watch stand up comedians or reruns of the Office and it’s amazing how that small change can help your mood lift. Helps you realize everything will be okay. 

- Practice gratitude ☮️
Depression has a AWESOME way of making you feel like there’s nothing to be grateful for. Write at least 3 things you are grateful for daily. I am not kidding you when I tell you this is such a great mind shift change. It takes practice trust me! Sometimes I could only get one thing down but I stayed consistent. 

- Watch the sunrise. 🌞
One thing I used to hate is waking up early…I have struggled with being a morning person trust me! I think it’s because with depression you’re just waking up to another day of pain. I started to make myself go to bed early so I could wake up for sunrise I yearned for this quiet moment in nature where no one was awake yet. Watching the sunrise gave me hope it gave me a different set of eyes that saw beauty in the world again. Adding this made the days more bearable this quiet moment I had with myself and nature. 

Please know that we all have different coping mechanism, while this work for me, there’s no guarantee that it will work for you. But don’t let that stop you! Get inspired and find something that makes you feel you again. 💜

#julydump #mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealthmatters #beachlife #sunshine #ocean

Cheers to 1 year sober from alcohol 🍻

Not everyday is sunshine and rainbows 🌈 I still have cloudy days but the sun shines through a lot more often. 

Meaning my bad days aren’t as bad as they used to be. I find new ways to overcome things besides drinking. 

Stressed - I go for a walk or exercise. 

Overthinking -  I journal or meditate 

Hating myself -  I shower or do skincare 

Depressed - I talk it through with my therapist or get out in nature 

I don’t care if I sound redundant. This shit works. I might forget or not do it everyday cause I wana be in my feels or life. 

But when I stay on that routine of reacting those ways to my triggers life is so much easier. 

I don’t say I’m proud of myself much but this is something I’m …so proud of. 

Thank you to anyone who reached out or has shown amazing support. 

Especially to my plant medicine mamas🍄

And thank you @abbeyjophotos for capturing my new glow ✨

Dear Fathers Dear EVERYONE,✨

Identifying when your antidepressant might not be effective:

- Your depression deepens.

- Immediate relief, but it fades.

- Sleep troubles.

- Your constantly tired

- Escalating suicidal thoughts.

( I’m sorry NO medication should make you feel this way)

My father faced an arduous mental health journey, trying numerous antidepressants. Regrettably, his last medication turned his suicidal thoughts into a grim reality.

I walked a similar path, trying every antidepressant, but I’m proud I didn’t heed the inner voice urging suicide trust me I heard it; I was over it and didn’t want to wait another 6 months to test another pill. 

I wish I could turn back time to introduce my dad to psychedelic remedies. While the past can’t be changed, today, I can help people discover alternatives to Big Pharma. 

Psychedelics were banned because they make you feel better way quicker than any anti depressant…but big pharma wants you stuck on a pill for the rest of your life because how else would they make money. 

Ask yourself this…did your doctor tell you when you can get off the meds? 

Do what works for you always…but know that there’s other options. 🙏🏼

Please never be afraid to slide in my DMs to learn more about other alternatives or if you’re struggling ✨ your mental health is everything 🫶🏼

Green living isn’t just a trend; it’s a mindful choice for a healthier mind 💚🧠

As the days grow shorter and the nights longer, it’s easy to feel the blues creeping in. Seasonal depression is a real thing, baby. But don’t worry, be happy—just kidding. Let’s do some shit that’ll make you feel better and benefit the planet.🌎 

- Skate 🛹, bike, walk whenever possible. Use this as a way to get outside, exercise 🌞, reduce your carbon footprint, and connect with nature.

- Grow your food 🌱. I can’t tell you how fulfilled and accomplished I feel when I grow something 😂. I know not everyone has space, so start with some herbs!

- Eat local 🥦. Go visit your farmers’ markets and support your farmers! I promise the serotonin you’ll feel at a farmers’ market—so many kinds of humans—you really get a sense of community. Visit all your local markets; engaging in sustainable initiatives fosters a sense of belonging and social support, which can help reduce any loneliness that can negatively impact your mental health.

Sustainable living can help reduce stress. When we’re doing things that are good for our planet, we feel good about ourselves. We know that we’re making a difference. 🫶🏼

For the holidays and gift-giving, try to stay local and look for B Corp companies! They meet rigorous standards for social and environmental performance, accountability, and transparency. 🤝🏼

@cariuma is a B Corp company, and now through Nov 27, they are planting 10 trees for every pair of shoes sold on their website instead of their usual 2. Their reforestation initiative helps restore biodiversity in the Brazilian rainforest.🌳

Let’s embrace the power of sunshine, exercise, connection, sustainable fashion, and supporting our local communities as we navigate through the highs and lows of seasonal depression.✨

Let’s make conscious choices that not only improve our mental wellbeing but also contribute to a healthier and more sustainable future.🫶🏼

#cariumapartner #mentalhealthmatters #sustainableliving #sustainablefashion
